The reranker implementation compiles and basic behavior works, but it introduces an unnecessary model load/network fetch on empty result sets when reranking is enabled.

Review comment:

- [P2] Avoid loading the reranker for empty result sets — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:4944-4944
  When `default-reranker` is enabled, `ce_rerank` calls `try_get_loaded()` before checking whether there are any hits to score. For a cold cache, an empty search result with `rerank_depth > 0` will therefore try to load/download the ~17 MB model only to return an empty vector, and a transient load failure is memoized for the process. Short-circuit `hits.is_empty()` before touching the singleton.
